    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required gradation levels. The single below-level factor (Test conditions, achieved gradation 2 vs. required 3) is mitigated by direct alignment of the single test configuration with ASTM F1717 and FDA regulatory requirements, and by the strong quantitative agreement demonstrated across all three QoI (maximum E/uval=0.74, maximum percent difference 1.6%). The overall credibility evidence is judged sufficient to support the intended regulatory submission use. Package accepted.",
